{"name": "cm-time", "metadata": {"name": "cm-time", "version": "0.1.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 2 - Pre-Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: CC0 1.0 Universal (CC0 1.0) Public Domain Dedication", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries"], "home_page": "https://github.com/34j/cm-time", "license": "CC0-1.0", "documentation_url": "https://cm-time.readthedocs.io", "dependencies": [], "summary": "A simple context manager that measures time using perf_counter()", "upload_time": 1678916712}, "documentation": ["# A Context Manager and A Decorator for Measuring Execution Time\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/34j/cm-time/actions?query=workflow%3ACI\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/workflow/status/34j/cm-time/CI/main?label=CI&logo=github&style=flat-square\" alt=\"CI Status\" >\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://cm-time.readthedocs.io\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/readthedocs/cm-time.svg?logo=read-the-docs&logoColor=fff&style=flat-square\" alt=\"Documentation Status\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://codecov.io/gh/34j/cm-time\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/codecov/c/github/34j/cm-time.svg?logo=codecov&logoColor=fff&style=flat-square\" alt=\"Test coverage percentage\">\n  </a>\n</p>\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <a href=\"https://python-poetry.org/\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/packaging-poetry-299bd7?style=flat-square&logo=data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"Poetry\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/ambv/black\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg?style=flat-square\" alt=\"black\">\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/pre--commit-enabled-brightgreen?logo=pre-commit&logoColor=white&style=flat-square\" alt=\"pre-commit\">\n  </a>\n</p>\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/cm-time/\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/cm-time.svg?logo=python&logoColor=fff&style=flat-square\" alt=\"PyPI Version\">\n  </a>\n  <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/cm-time.svg?style=flat-square&logo=python&amp;logoColor=fff\" alt=\"Supported Python versions\">\n  <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/cm-time.svg?style=flat-square\" alt=\"License\">\n</p>\n\nA simple context manager that measures time using perf_counter()\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall this via pip (or your favourite package manager):\n\n`pip install cm-time`\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nfrom cm_time import timer\n\nwith timer() as t:\n      pass\n\nprint(t.elapsed)\n```\n\nOutput:\n\n```shell\nElapsed time: 0.000\n0.0\n```\n\n```python\nfrom cm_time import timer_wrapped\n\n@timer_wrapped()\ndef foo():\n    pass\n```\n\nOutput:\n\n```shell\nfoo: Elapsed time: 0.000\n```\n\n## Contributors \u2728\n\nThanks goes to these wonderful people ([emoji key](https://allcontributors.org/docs/en/emoji-key)):\n\n<!-- prettier-ignore-start -->\n<!-- ALL-CONTRIBUTORS-LIST:START - Do not remove or modify this section -->\n<!-- markdownlint-disable -->\n<!-- markdownlint-enable -->\n<!-- ALL-CONTRIBUTORS-LIST:END -->\n<!-- prettier-ignore-end -->\n\nThis project follows the [all-contributors](https://github.com/all-contributors/all-contributors) specification. Contributions of any kind welcome!\n\n## Credits\n\nThis package was created with\n[Copier](https://copier.readthedocs.io/) and the\n[browniebroke/pypackage-template](https://github.com/browniebroke/pypackage-template)\nproject template.\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "cm_time", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "cm_time.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "cm_time.timer", "xref": {"fqname": "cm_time.main.timer", "project": null}}, {"name": "cm_time.timer_wrapped", "xref": {"fqname": "cm_time.main.timer_wrapped", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "cm_time.main", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "cm_time.main.timer_wrapped", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "message", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "logger", "type": {"name": "Logger | EllipsisType | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "level", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "", "xref": null, "params": [{"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "_TParams", "xref": null, "params": null}, {"name": "_TResult", "xref": {"fqname": "_TResult", "project": null}, "params": null}]}]}, {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "_TParams", "xref": null, "params": null}, {"name": "_TResult", "xref": {"fqname": "_TResult", "project": null}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": ["A decorator that measures the time elapsed in a block of code.\nAsynchronous functions are supported.\n\nParameters\n----------\nmessage : str, optional\n    Message to log. Must contain a single format specifier\n    for the elapsed time, by default \"Elapsed time: {:.3f}\"\nlogger : Logger | None, optional\n    Logger to use, by default None\n    If ... (default), use getLogger(func.__module__)\nlevel : int, optional\n    Level to log at, by default INFO\n\nReturns\n-------\nCallable[[Callable[_TParams, _TResult]], Callable[_TParams, _TResult]]\n    Wrapped function."]}], "variables": [{"name": "cm_time.ma